title: v1.4 RELEASE (#168)
message:
v1.4 RELEASE (#168)

* Planer events with the canceled flag are marked.
* Add unit- and instrumentation tests
* Move to CircleCI continues integration
* Refactored Logout, SignIn to new app architecture
* Workaround: Reset ObjectGraph on logout. Before this change the Endpoint URL would be retained after logout since the Retrofit instance is marked as Singleton.
* Update libs
* Move Course and Planner fragment scopes to @PerFragment, maybe fixes #164 fixes #159 and possibly other
* Version bump
* Support for Android 8
* Fixes #167
* Fixes #165

* Version bump

title: Fix downloads on Android versions < API 18
message:
Fix downloads on Android versions < API 18

Due to improper SSL certificate handling on both Android and server sites, SSL connections on these versions fail if the internal HTTP stack is used. That's why only a downgrade to HTTP is a solution.

title: Move JNI lib init to DatabaseHandler instance
message:
Move JNI lib init to DatabaseHandler instance

It's possible that the JNI will not be initialized after the App resumes
after suspension. Moving to the DatabaseHandler instance should ensure
that the libs are initialized everytime the database is requestet.
Loading shared libs multiple times should'nt have a impact on
performance.

title: Load users immediately, assign courses to semesters while inserting
message:
Load users immediately, assign courses to semesters while inserting

- Removed the whole pending users sync queue logic.
It was too error-prone and not good implemented.
Instead an async task is used now immediately when the response comes
back.
- The correct semesters are now assigned before inserting into the db.
This removes the error-prone sort logic in the CoursesFragment.
